{
  "id": "4",
  "title": "4. Headless Pipeline Runs & CI/CD Orchestration",
  "type": "lab",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Executing Agent Workloads in CI/CD"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "To scale agentic engineering, agent loops must run unattended in continuous integration pipelines. A headless run executes without user interaction, reading task instructions, running files, performing checks, and reporting results. This requires configuring non-interactive authorization, defining timeout thresholds, and capturing build artifacts."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> [!WARNING]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> Because headless pipelines cannot request human-in-the-loop approvals, any CLI invocation must include the --auto-approve flag or a custom workspace rule file (.gemini.md) specifying permitted actions. Ensure strict repository branch protections are active so agents cannot run unreviewed code changes."
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Production-Grade GitLab CI/CD Configuration"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "The following GitLab CI/CD snippet runs a headless agent sequence inside an ephemeral agy-box workspace, processing a pull request and generating a test coverage report."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "stages:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- analyze",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "run_headless_agent:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "stage: analyze",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "image: private-registry.corp.internal/agy/agy-box:latest",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "variables:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "AGY_WORKSPACE_DIR: \"$CI_PROJECT_DIR\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "AGY_HEADLESS: \"true\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "AGY_API_KEY: \"$AGY_PROD_API_KEY\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "before_script:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Setup isolated temporary directory within workspace",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "mkdir -p $CI_PROJECT_DIR/.tmp",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "export TMPDIR=$CI_PROJECT_DIR/.tmp",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Verify API authorization credentials",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "agy --version",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "agy auth verify --token $AGY_API_KEY",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "script:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# Execute the agent loop on the workspace.",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# --auto-approve allows executing commands without human prompts.",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "# --timeout 600 limits execution time to 10 minutes.",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "agy run \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--task \"Refactor the unit tests in tests/ to resolve legacy assertion warnings\" \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--auto-approve \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--timeout 600 \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--rules-file .gemini.md",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "artifacts:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "name: agent-changes",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "paths:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- tests/",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- agy-report.json",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "expire_in: 7 days",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Advanced CI/CD Pipeline Automation (GitHub Actions)"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "GitHub Actions can also run headless agent operations. We use actions secrets to pass API keys securely and checkout only the specific pull request branch."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "name: Headless Agent Automation",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "on:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "pull_request:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "paths:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- 'src/**'",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "jobs:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "run-agent:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "runs-on: ubuntu-latest",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "steps:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- name: Checkout Repository",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "uses: actions/checkout@v3",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "with:",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "ref: ${{ github.event.pull_request.head.ref }}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "fetch-depth: 0",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- name: Run Ephemeral AGY-Box Sandbox",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "run: |",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "docker run --rm \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "-v ${{ github.workspace }}:/workspace \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "-e AGY_API_KEY=${{ secrets.AGY_API_KEY }} \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "-e GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/workspace/gcp-creds.json \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "private-registry.corp.internal/agy/agy-box:latest \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "agy run \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--task \"Run automated security scan on src/ and fix vulnerabilities\" \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--auto-approve \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--workspace /workspace \\",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "--output-report /workspace/agy-report.json",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "- name: Commit Agent Suggestions",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "run: |",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "git config --global user.name \"AGY Headless Runner\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "git config --global user.email \"agy-runner@corp.internal\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "git add src/",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "git diff-index --quiet HEAD || git commit -m \"style: automated agent security refactoring\"",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "content": "git push origin HEAD:${{ github.event.pull_request.head.ref }}",
      "language": "bash"
    },
    {
      "type": "h3",
      "content": "Check Your Understanding"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 1: What flag must be provided to the agy CLI during a headless run to prevent the pipeline from hanging indefinitely while waiting for user confirmation?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A) --verbose"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "B) --auto-approve"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "C) --no-sandbox"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "D) --headless"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> [!NOTE]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> Correct Answer: B. Headless pipelines do not have interactive terminals. The --auto-approve flag forces the CLI to auto-verify and execute agent actions without pausing for manual approvals."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Question 2: How should security sensitive API keys be passed to the containerized agy-box inside a CI/CD job?"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "A) Hardcoded into the GitLab CI/CD yaml file."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "B) Injected dynamically via environment variables sourced from CI/CD repository secrets."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "C) Stored in a public git repository."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "D) Sourced from a local text file inside the home directory."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> [!NOTE]"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "> Correct Answer: B. CI/CD secrets variables keep credentials out of version control and pass them to the job at runtime as secure environment variables."
    }
  ]
}